Inspect demo data uploaded to JAMES

Source: R/inspect_demodata.R
inspect_demodata.Rd

Uploads JSON child demo data to localhost and downloads the processed data for inspection.

inspect_demodata(
  name,
  cabinet,
  format = c("2.0", "1.0", "1.1"),
  host = "http://localhost",
  mod = character(0)
)

Arguments

name

Name of the child

cabinet

Name of cabinet

format

String. JSON data schema version number. There are currently three schemas supported: "1.0", "1.1" and "2.0". Formats "1.0" and "1.1" are included for backward compatibility only. Use format = "2.0" for new applications.

host

String with the host. The default is "http://localhost".

mod

String with the module path, if any. The default is "".

Examples

data <- inspect_demodata(name = "Anne_S", cabinet = "smocc")
